HEADWORD: Chylifaction
<hw>Chyl`i*fac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Chyle</ets> + L. <ets>facere</ets> to make.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The act or process by which chyle is formed
from food in animal bodies; chylification, -- a digestive
process.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

